		<div id="section0">
			<h1>Architecture</h1>
			<p>
				The GTB (Global Transaction Banking) system formerly ScotiaConnect Online new architecture system from the SCP (Software Currency Project) initiative. For a background of the migration and strategy please see the
				<a href="http://sdt78hpaty1/svn/scotia/SCO/WebSphere%205%20Migration/Business%20Analysis/Migration%20Roadmap.pdf" target="_blank">Migration RoadMap</a>
				and the
				<a href="http://sdt78hpaty1/svn/scotia/SCO/WebSphere%205%20Migration/Migration%20Strategy%20-%20managed%20transition.pdf">Managed Transition</a>
				diagram.
			</p>
			<p>
				The N-tier or layered design of the system follows the J2EE (Java 2 Platform Enterprise Edition) architecture, a reliable, scalable and secure platform for developing client to server applications and web services in Java. The J2EE specifications, application programming model (BluePrints) and related information is available at
				<a href="http://java.sun.com/j2ee/" target="_blank">http://java.sun.com/j2ee/</a>
				. Further to this, the N-tier and J2EE architecture has facilities for enablement of SOA (services oriented architecture).
			</p>
		</div>
		<div id="section1">
			<h2>Summary of Tiers</h2>
			<p>Primary architecture mandates are as follows,</p>
			<div>
				<ul>
					<li>Loosely couple the tiers and technologies.</li>
					<li>Reference the Core J2EE Patterns.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
